    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,

</t><stat>SELECT t.team_name, COUNT(*) AS total_players FROM SportsTeam t JOIN Player p ON t.team_id = p.team_id GROUP BY t.team_id HAVING total_players > 5;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE SportsTeam (
    team_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sport_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE Player (
    player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    team_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES SportsTeam(team_id)
);
</t><stat>select t.team_name, count(*) as total_players from sportsteam t join player p on t.team_id = p.team_id group by t.team_id having total_players > 5;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Player (
    player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    team_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES SportsTeam(team_id)
);


CREATE TABLE SportsTeam (
    team_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sport_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>SELECT t.team_name, COUNT(*) AS total_players FROM SportsTeam t JOIN Player p ON t.team_id = p.team_id GROUP BY t.team_id HAVING total_players > 5;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Player (
    player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    team_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES SportsTeam(team_id)
);


CREATE TABLE SportsTeam (
    team_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sport_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>select t.team_name, count(*) as total_players from sportsteam t join player p on t.team_id = p.team_id group by t.team_id having total_players > 5;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE SportsTeam (
    team_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sport_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE Player (
    player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    team_id INT,

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><stat>SELECT * FROM teams;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><stat>SELECT t1.team_name AS team1_name, t2.team_name AS team2_name FROM matches m JOIN teams t1 ON m.team1_id = t1.team_id JOIN teams t2 ON m.team2_id = t2.team_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><stat>SELECT team_name, AVG(player_id) AS avg_players FROM teams JOIN players ON teams.team_id = players.team_id GROUP BY team_name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><stat>SELECT team_name, MIN(player_id) AS min_player_id FROM teams JOIN players ON teams.team_id = players.team_id GROUP BY team_name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(50), team_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));

CREATE TABLE matches (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE, team1_id INT, team2_id INT, winner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (team1_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (team2_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id), FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES teams(team_id));</t><stat>SELECT team_name, match_date, CASE WHEN match_date <= '2022-02-28' THEN 'Past Match' ELSE 'Upcoming Match' END AS match_status FROM teams JOIN matches ON teams.team_id = matches.team1_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE team (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><stat>SELECT team1_id, team2_id, stadium_name FROM match INNER JOIN stadium ON match.team1_id = stadium.stadium_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)</t><stat>select team1_id, team2_id, stadium_name from match inner join stadium on match.team1_id = stadium.stadium_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><stat>SELECT team1_id, team2_id, stadium_name FROM match INNER JOIN stadium ON match.team1_id = stadium.stadium_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)
